{{Wikiversity|Children Sleep Habits Questionnaire}}
The '''Children’s Sleep Habits Questionnaire (CSHQ)''' is a psychological questionnaire designed to measure [[sleep]] behaviors in children and adolescents ages 4-12. The 52-question test is filled out by the parent and takes approximately 10 minutes to complete.  The CSHQ has demonstrated good [[Reliability (psychometrics)|reliability]] and [[Test validity|validity]] in measuring child sleep habits and problems. <ref name=GoodlinJonesEtAl2008/> <ref name=OwensEtAl2000/>

