{{Infobox journal | title = Evaluation & the Health Professions | cover = Evaluation & the Health Professions.tif | editor = Steve Sussman | discipline = [[Health sciences]] | former_names = | abbreviation = Eval. Health Prof. | publisher = [[Sage Publications]] | country = | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1978-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = 1.909 | impact-year = 2014 | website = http://www.sagepub.com/journals/Journal200787/title | link1 = http://ehp.sagepub.com/content/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://ehp.sagepub.com/content/by/year | link2-name = Online archive | JSTOR = | OCLC = 3945887 | LCCN = 78646612 | CODEN = | ISSN = 0163-2787 | eISSN = 1552-3918 }} '''''Evaluation & the Health Professions''''' is a [[peer-reviewed]] [[public health journal]] that covers all aspects of the [[evaluation]] of [[health care]]. The founding [[editor-in-chief|editors-in-chief]] were [[R. Barker Bausell]] and Carolyn F. Waltz ([[University of Maryland, Baltimore]]),<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Sussman|first1=S.|title=A Content Analysis of Evaluation & the Health Professions Over 32 Years|journal=Evaluation & the Health Professions|date=17 February 2010|volume=33|issue=1|pages=7–11|doi=10.1177/0163278709360274|pmid=20164103|pmc=4181560}}</ref> and the current one is Steve Sussman ([[University of Southern California]]). The journal was established in 1978 and is published by [[Sage Publications]].
